verbose_text: IL-17 induces the production of other cytokines, [IL-6, TGF-beta, tumor necrosis factor (TNF)-alpha, granulocyte colony stimulating factor, granulocyte-macrophage colony stimulating factor and IL-1beta], chemokines (IL-8, growth regulated oncogene-alpha and monocyte chemoattractant protein-1), and prostaglandin, including prostaglandin E2, from fibroblasts, endothelial cells and several other cell types.
